ŠIn Loving Memory of Sarah Jane Johnson (nee Parr)
24 October. 1978 - 27 April 2015
Adored Wife, Mother, Sister, Daughter and cherished Friend
Rest in Peace Gorgeous Girl. Big Kisses x x x"┼
┬As a small boy not far from this very spot, he began running and did not stop
Far across the globe he ran, this beloved, crazy, brilliant man
He loved wine. music and the southern sun, he always gave his best to everyone
He is much missed and that he should, for our south London boy did good
Vincent Hancock 1944-2006"═
╩in Loving Memory of BRIAN MIST Naturalist and Conservationist
For his Work and Dedication to the Park
Who Died 8th May 2002 - Age 65
Sadly missed by his wife Rosie and son Bradley and all his friends"Ž
╠BRIAN BOTTING FRICS 1932 2014
First Chairman of the Friends of Battersea Park 1990- 1999
The Hungarian Oak opposite was planted in his memory
A great servant of the Park with a mischievous sense of fun"█
žIn Loving Memory of Georgi "Porgy" Todorov 1978 2005
"It's not the years in your life that count...
It's the life in your years" We will never forget your
smile, you are forever our inspiration. We miss you Porg x"█
